The paper deals with mining social media data to understand illicit drug use behaviors, which falls under the category of social media analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves natural language processing techniques to analyze the text data, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also deals with privacy and security concerns related to social media data, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper involves studying the behavior of drug users, which falls under the category of social computing (cs.SOC).
